The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) codes, which are primarily studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The problem of minimizing the number of encoded bits given the values of $s$ and $k$ involves combinatorial optimization, which is a topic studied in the data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) as it deals with encoding information in a specific way.
